# Learning chapter template
#
# Save this file as e.g. `ch01-introduction-and-homeostasis.md` (the
# filename's basename, sans `.md`, becomes the URL slug). Then fill
# in the four layer sections below. Any layer you leave out is hidden
# from the tab strip — author what you have, ship the rest later.
#
# ---
# chapter: Chapter 1 — Introduction to Physiology and Homeostasis
# part: Part I — Foundations of Physiology
# status: draft
# ---
#
# # Layer 1 — Core
#
# 30-second elevator description of the chapter. The single most
# important sentence-or-paragraph a learner should walk away with.
# Bullet points OK. Keep it tight.
#
# # Layer 2 — Working
#
# Two-to-three-minute working explanation. The level a competent
# first-year MBBS student should be able to recite. Diagrams welcome
# (use Markdown image syntax, drop the file via the admin upload tool).
#
# # Layer 3 — Deep Dive
#
# Eight-to-ten-minute deeper read. The mechanism's nuance, the
# experimental evidence, the edge cases, the historical context, the
# cross-system integrations. This is where the review-book detail
# lives.
#
# # Layer 4 — Clinical Integration
#
# How the chapter shows up at bedside. Diseases that disrupt the
# mechanism, drug classes that target it, common patient presentations,
# differential reasoning. Anchors the chapter in clinical practice.
#
# # Sources
#
# Optional. Bulleted list of references — Guyton, Costanzo, Sherwood,
# Ganong, primary literature. Surfaced as a small footer below the
# layer tabs.
